{
 "response": "# Perspective Audit \u2014 SubscribeModal / SubscribePage (Modal Dialog With Broken Focus Trap)\n\n## Step 1 \u2014 Escalated perspectives confirmed\n\nAlarm levels supplied by the a11y-critic:\n\n| Perspective | Alarm | Deep review? |\n|---|---|---|\n| Keyboard & Motor Access (5) | **HIGH** | Yes |\n| Screen Reader & Semantic Structure (6) | **HIGH** | Yes |\n| Cognitive & Neurodivergent (7) | **MEDIUM** | Yes |\n| Magnification & Reflow (1) | LOW | No \u2014 not reviewed |\n| Environmental Contrast (2) | LOW | No \u2014 not reviewed |\n| Vestibular & Motion (3) | LOW | No \u2014 not reviewed |\n| Auditory Access (4) | LOW | No \u2014 not reviewed |\n\nThree perspectives escalated to MEDIUM/HIGH. Checklists below run only for those three.\n\n**Calibration note before findings (naming the trap in the fixture title):** the fixture is called \"broken focus trap,\" but the defect is a *missing* focus trap, not a WCAG 2.1.2 keyboard-trap violation. 2.1.2 No Keyboard Trap is about focus being *unable to escape* a component; here focus escapes too freely. A checklist-driven reviewer would reflexively cite 2.1.2 here and be wrong. The real barriers are focus-management gaps (2.4.3) and absent dialog semantics (4.1.2/4.1.3). Severities below reflect user impact, not the alarming filename.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 5 \u2014 Keyboard & Motor Access (HIGH)\n\n### Step 4 checklist results\n\n| # | Checklist item (WCAG) | Result | Evidence |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | All interactive elements reachable/operable by keyboard (2.1.1) | **PASS** | All controls are real `<button>`/`<input>` \u2014 trigger (line 137-144), close \u00d7, name/email inputs (82-102), Cancel/Subscribe (107-112). No `div`-as-button, no `onKeyDown` reimplementation. |\n| 2 | No keyboard trap (2.1.2) | **PASS** | Tab/Shift+Tab always move freely; Cancel and \u00d7 close the modal. Focus is *never* trapped. (The problem is the inverse \u2014 see Finding 5.3.) |\n| 3 | Skip link targets main content (2.4.1) | **N/A** | Single-component fixture; no page-level repeated blocks in scope. |\n| 4 | Focus order follows logical sequence (2.4.3) | **FINDING** | See 5.1, 5.2, 5.3. |\n| 5 | Focus indicator \u22652px, \u22653:1 contrast (2.4.7) | **PASS** | Every interactive element has `outline: 3px solid #1565c0; outline-offset: 2px` (CSS lines 182-185, 232-235, 257-261, 281-284, 297-300, 320-323). 3px \u2265 2px; #1565c0 on white \u2248 5.9:1. Genuine strength. |\n| 6 | Multi-point gestures have single-pointer alt (2.5.1) | **N/A** | No gestures. |\n| 7 | Activation on up-event (2.5.2) | **PASS** | React `onClick` fires on pointer-up; no `onMouseDown` activation. |\n| 8 | Visible label matches accessible name (2.5.3) | **FINDING (cross-ref 6.3)** | Cancel/Subscribe: visible text = accessible name (PASS). Close \u00d7 has *no* accessible name \u2014 voice-control users cannot say \"click close.\" Rooted in the missing name (4.1.2); primary finding routed to Perspective 6. |\n| 9 | Every drag has click alternative (2.5.7) | **N/A** | No drag. |\n| 10 | Targets \u226524\u00d724 CSS px (2.5.8) | **PASS** | Close: 24px glyph + 4px\u00d72 padding \u2248 32\u00d730px. Buttons/inputs exceed 24px via padding. |\n| 11 | Portrait and landscape both work (1.3.4) | **PASS** | Flex-centered, `max-width` container; no orientation lock. |\n\n**Red flags (auto-CRITICAL) checked:** unreachable element \u2014 no. Keyboard trap \u2014 no. Drag-only \u2014 no. `outline:none` with no replacement \u2014 no. **None fire.** For a sighted keyboard-only user the modal is fully operable and can be completed and dismissed; the harm is disorientation, not blockage. That ceiling is why the keyboard findings land at MAJOR, not CRITICAL \u2014 correct for a HIGH (not CRITICAL-saturated) alarm.\n\n### Findings\n\n**Finding:** Focus is not moved into the dialog when it opens. On clicking \"Subscribe Now\" focus stays on the trigger button behind the backdrop; because the modal is rendered *after* the background `<nav>` in the DOM (line 153), the keyboard user's next Tab lands on the background Home/About/Contact links before ever reaching the modal.\n**WCAG:** 2.4.3 Focus Order\n**Perspective:** Keyboard & Motor Access\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** Component comments confirm the gap \u2014 \"No useEffect to move focus into the modal on open\" (lines 23-25); trigger/render order at lines 137-144 and 153. No `ref` on `.modal-container`, no focus call on mount.\n**Fix:** On open, move focus to the first focusable element (the close button or name input) or to the dialog container with `tabIndex={-1}`, via a `useEffect` keyed to mount.\n\n**Finding:** Focus is not restored to the trigger when the modal closes. `handleClose` tears down the modal but never calls `triggerRef.current.focus()`, so focus drops to `<body>` and the keyboard user loses their place entirely.\n**WCAG:** 2.4.3 Focus Order\n**Perspective:** Keyboard & Motor Access\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `handleClose` at lines 127-130 with the explicit comment \"Missing: triggerRef.current?.focus();\". `triggerRef` is attached (line 138) but never read.\n**Fix:** In `handleClose` (and after successful submit dismissal), call `triggerRef.current?.focus()` so focus returns to \"Subscribe Now.\"\n\n**Finding:** No focus containment \u2014 background controls stay in the tab order while the modal is open. Tabbing forward or backward moves focus onto the background nav links and page content, which sit *underneath* the dimmed backdrop, so the focus ring effectively disappears from view for the user.\n**WCAG:** 2.4.3 Focus Order\n**Perspective:** Keyboard & Motor Access\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** Comment \"No focus trap logic \u2014 Tab exits into background page freely\" (line 25); \"Background content remains fully interactive while modal is open\" (line 146); background `<nav>` at lines 147-151 has no `inert`/`aria-hidden`.\n**Fix:** Contain Tab/Shift+Tab within the dialog (wrap at first/last focusable), and mark background content `inert` (or `aria-hidden=\"true\"`) while open \u2014 this also delivers the `aria-modal` behavior needed by Perspective 6.\n[Note: the \"focus lands on visually obscured background\" effect touches 2.4.11 Focus Not Obscured, owned by the Magnification perspective, which was rated LOW and is not separately reviewed here \u2014 recorded as consequence only.]\n\n**Finding:** The dialog cannot be dismissed with the Escape key. There is no `keydown` handler; dismissal requires locating and activating the Cancel or \u00d7 control.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value (dialog interaction contract per WAI-ARIA APG) \u2014 *[APG authoring convention; not a distinct WCAG 2.2 AA success criterion on its own]*\n**Perspective:** Keyboard & Motor Access\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** No `onKeyDown`/Escape handling anywhere in `SubscribeModal`; expected-behavior spec calls for \"Escape closes the modal.\"\n**Fix:** Add an Escape `keydown` listener on the dialog that invokes `onClose`. Workaround exists today (Cancel button), hence MINOR \u2014 but Escape is expected once `role=\"dialog\"` is present.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 6 \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic Structure (HIGH)\n\n### Step 4 checklist results\n\n| # | Checklist item (WCAG) | Result | Evidence |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Landmarks present/correct (1.3.1) | **PASS (page) / FINDING (dialog)** | `<main>` (133) and `<nav>` (147) present. The overlay carries no dialog role \u2014 see 6.1. |\n| 2 | Heading hierarchy logical, h1 present (2.4.6) | **PASS** | `<h1>Newsletter</h1>` (134) \u2192 `<h2 id=\"modal-title\">` (64); no skipped level. (Success view drops the heading \u2014 minor, folded into 6.4.) |\n| 3 | Informative images have alt; decorative alt=\"\" (1.1.1) | **N/A** | No `<img>`. The \u00d7 is a text glyph, not an image. |\n| 4 | DOM order matches reading order (1.3.2) | **FINDING (folded into 6.1)** | Modal rendered after background nav (153); with no `aria-modal`, SR reading order reaches modal content last, after background content. |\n| 5 | Unique descriptive `<title>` (2.4.2) | **N/A** | No document `<title>` in component scope. |\n| 6 | Link text describes destination (2.4.4) | **PASS** | \"Home\"/\"About\"/\"Contact\" self-describing. |\n| 7 | `lang` on `<html>` (3.1.1) | **N/A** | No `<html>` in scope. |\n| 8 | Foreign phrases wrapped in `lang` (3.1.2) | **N/A** | None present. |\n| 9 | Every input has associated visible label (3.3.2) | **PASS** | Name: `<label htmlFor=\"modal-name\">` + `id=\"modal-name\"` (82-84). Email: `<label htmlFor=\"modal-email\">` + `id=\"modal-email\"` (95-97). Correct, visible, programmatic. Genuine strength \u2014 the form fields themselves are exemplary. |\n| 10 | Errors identify field, associated via `aria-describedby` (3.3.1) | **FINDING (see P7 F7.2)** | No error mechanism exists at all (`noValidate` line 77 + `handleSubmit` sets `submitted` with no validation, 27-30). Nothing to associate; the latent gap is owned by the validation finding in Perspective 7. |\n| 11 | Custom widgets use correct ARIA roles per APG (4.1.2) | **FINDING** | See 6.1, 6.2, 6.3. |\n| 12 | Status messages use `aria-live` (4.1.3) | **FINDING** | See 6.4. |\n| 13 | SPA-style change: title/focus/announce | **FINDING (folded into 6.1/6.4)** | Open and submit are unannounced content changes with no focus management. |\n\n**Red flags (auto-CRITICAL) checked:** no `<main>` \u2014 main is present (PASS). Inputs without any label \u2014 labels present (PASS). **Custom widget with no ARIA role \u2014 FIRES:** the modal overlay has no `role=\"dialog\"`. Missing `lang` \u2014 N/A (component scope). One red flag fires \u2192 auto-CRITICAL (Finding 6.1).\n\n### Findings\n\n**Finding:** The modal overlay exposes no dialog semantics \u2014 no `role=\"dialog\"` (or `role=\"alertdialog\"`) and no `aria-modal=\"true\"`. A screen-reader user is never told a dialog opened; the content is announced as ordinary inline page content, and the virtual cursor can read straight into the still-exposed background page. The trigger advertises `aria-haspopup=\"dialog\"` (line 141), so the SR promises a dialog that never structurally arrives \u2014 a broken contract.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** CRITICAL *(auto-CRITICAL red flag: custom widget with no ARIA role)*\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** Both `.modal-backdrop`/`.modal-container` wrappers (form view line 59; success view line 39) are plain `<div>`s. Comments confirm: \"No role='dialog'\u2026 No aria-modal='true'\u2026 background content not hidden to virtual cursor\" (lines 53-58); `aria-haspopup=\"dialog\"` at line 141.\n**Fix:** Add `role=\"dialog\"` and `aria-modal=\"true\"` to `.modal-container`, and pair with the containment/`inert` fix from Finding 5.3 so background content is genuinely removed from the accessibility tree while open.\n\n**Finding:** The dialog has no accessible name. `<h2 id=\"modal-title\">` exists but nothing references it \u2014 there is no `aria-labelledby=\"modal-title\"` (nor `aria-label`). Even after a dialog role is added, the SR would announce only \"dialog\" with no title.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: Content Author)\n**Evidence:** Comment \"id present for potential aria-labelledby \u2014 but dialog never references it\" (line 63); heading at line 64; no `aria-labelledby` on either wrapper.\n**Fix:** Add `aria-labelledby=\"modal-title\"` to the `role=\"dialog\"` container so it announces \"Subscribe to Updates, dialog.\" (Success view: give that state its own heading and label target \u2014 see 6.4.)\n\n**Finding:** The close button has no accessible name. Its only content is the \"\u00d7\" glyph, so screen readers announce \"times,\" \"multiplication sign,\" or just \"button\" depending on the SR/verbosity \u2014 never \"Close.\" This affects both the form view and the success view, where \u00d7 is the *only* control and its purpose is unknowable to a non-visual user.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: Content Author)\n**Evidence:** `<button className=\"modal-close\" onClick={onClose}>\u00d7</button>` \u2014 form view lines 69-74, success view line 46. Comments at 42-45 and 65-68 confirm the missing name. No `aria-label`, no visually-hidden text.\n**Fix:** Add `aria-label=\"Close\"` (or `aria-label=\"Close dialog\"`) to both close buttons, keeping the \"\u00d7\" as `aria-hidden` decorative glyph. Exact wording is a Content Author decision (see Open Questions).\n\n**Finding:** The subscription-success confirmation is never announced. On submit, the modal content is replaced by `<p className=\"modal-success\">Thanks, {name}! You're subscribed.</p>` inside a region with no `role=\"status\"`, `role=\"alert\"`, or `aria-live`. Combined with the absent focus management, a screen-reader user pressing \"Subscribe\" receives no feedback that the action succeeded \u2014 the DOM changed silently.\n**WCAG:** 4.1.3 Status Messages\n**Perspective:** Screen Reader & Semantic Structure\n**Severity:** MAJOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** Submitted branch lines 32-49; success paragraph line 41 has class `modal-success` only (CSS 302-307) \u2014 no live-region role/attribute anywhere.\n**Fix:** Announce the confirmation via `role=\"status\"` (polite) on the success text, and/or move focus to the success heading on submit. Give the success state a heading and `aria-labelledby` so, with the dialog role, it reads as a labeled confirmation dialog.\n\n---\n\n## Perspective 7 \u2014 Cognitive & Neurodivergent (MEDIUM)\n\n### Step 4 checklist results\n\n| # | Checklist item (WCAG) | Result | Evidence |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Error messages suggest specific correction (3.3.3) | **FINDING** | See 7.2. |\n| 2 | Multi-step form doesn't re-ask info (3.3.7) | **N/A** | Single step. |\n| 3 | Auth: no cognitive test; paste/autofill work (3.3.8) | **PASS/N/A** | No auth. No `onPaste` blocking on inputs. |\n| 4 | Navigation same position across pages (3.2.3) | **N/A** | Single component. |\n| 5 | Same-function components consistent (3.2.4) | **PASS** | \u00d7 and Cancel both dismiss and are conventional; form-view and success-view \u00d7 are consistent. |\n| 6 | Help mechanism same location (3.2.6) | **N/A** | No help mechanism. |\n| 7 | Focus does not auto-trigger context change (3.2.1) | **PASS** | No `onFocus` handlers; modal opens on click, not focus. |\n| 8 | Changing a value doesn't auto-submit/navigate (3.2.2) | **PASS** | `onChange` only calls `setName`/`setEmail` (85-88, 98-101). |\n| 9 | Destructive actions have undo/confirmation (3.3.4) | **N/A** | Subscribing is not legal/financial/data-deletion; discarding an in-progress subscribe form is low-stakes. |\n| 10 | More than one way to reach a page (2.4.5) | **N/A** | Component scope. |\n| 11 | Personal-data inputs have `autocomplete` (1.3.5) | **FINDING** | See 7.1. |\n| 12 | Timeout warnings give \u226520s (2.2.1) | **N/A** | No timeout. |\n| 13 | Avoids jargon / complex sentences | **PASS** | \"Subscribe to Updates,\" \"Your name,\" \"Email address,\" \"Thanks, you're subscribed\" \u2014 plain language. |\n| ND | No autoplay / unprompted modal | **PASS** | Modal is user-triggered by clicking \"Subscribe Now\" \u2014 prompted, not autoplay. |\n| ND | Predictable layout / no unexpected shift | **NOTE** | On submit the full modal body is swapped for a one-line success message with no announcement/focus move \u2014 disorienting; the accessibility fix is covered by 6.4. |\n| ND | Instructions don't rely on memory | **PASS** | Single-step, self-contained. |\n\n**Red flags (auto-CRITICAL) checked:** CAPTCHA/cognitive test \u2014 no. Paste disabled \u2014 no. Multi-step redundant entry \u2014 no. Destructive action without confirmation \u2014 no. **None fire.** Deep review confirms the MEDIUM alarm was calibrated correctly: real gaps exist but none reach MAJOR/CRITICAL for this perspective.\n\n### Findings\n\n**Finding:** The name and email inputs collect personal data but carry no `autocomplete` attributes, so browser/AT autofill cannot pre-populate them. Users who rely on autofill to reduce typing and memory load must enter data manually, and personalization tools can't identify the field purpose.\n**WCAG:** 1.3.5 Identify Input Purpose\n**Perspective:** Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** Name input lines 82-89 and email input lines 95-102 \u2014 `type`, `id`, `required`, `aria-required` present; no `autocomplete`.\n**Fix:** Add `autocomplete=\"name\"` to the name field and `autocomplete=\"email\"` to the email field.\n\n**Finding:** The form promises required fields but never validates or reports errors. Both inputs carry `required` and `aria-required=\"true\"`, yet the form is `noValidate` and `handleSubmit` only sets `submitted = true` \u2014 so an empty or malformed email is silently \"accepted\" and the success message renders (e.g., \"Thanks, ! You're subscribed\" with an empty name). There is no error message, so there is nothing to suggest a correction. For cognitive users this is a misleading affordance: the interface claims a requirement it does not enforce and gives no feedback when data is wrong.\n**WCAG:** 3.3.3 Error Suggestion (and 3.3.1 Error Identification \u2014 no error is ever identified)\n**Perspective:** Cognitive & Neurodivergent\n**Severity:** MINOR\n**Route to:** Front-End Dev (secondary: UX Design)\n**Evidence:** `noValidate` at line 77; `handleSubmit` lines 27-30 (`e.preventDefault(); setSubmitted(true);` \u2014 no checks); `required`/`aria-required` at 87-88 and 100-101.\n**Fix:** Either remove the false `required`/`noValidate` contradiction, or add real validation: on invalid submit, render a specific, corrective message (\"Enter a valid email address, e.g. name@example.com\"), associate it to the field via `aria-describedby`, set `aria-invalid`, and move focus to the first field in error. Severity is MINOR because the happy path gives clear confirmation and manual correct entry is possible \u2014 but the misleading \"required\" markup should not ship as-is.\n\n---\n\n## Step 5 \u2014 Contract-compatible blocks (new CRITICAL / MAJOR findings)\n\nThe invocation was a prose critic escalation, so no upstream `finding_id`/`fingerprint` was supplied; the following blocks are emitted fresh for the CRITICAL and MAJOR findings surfaced in deep review. ARRM routing above remains authoritative for ownership.\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: modal-dialog-no-role-aria-modal\nfingerprint: a11y6f1c4d3e9b02\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic Structure checklist (item 11, red flag)\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value / WAI-ARIA APG Dialog (Modal) pattern\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 incorporates WCAG 2.0 A/AA; 4.1.2 is in scope\nseverity: CRITICAL\nperspective_alarms: keyboard_motor=HIGH, screen_reader_semantic=HIGH, cognitive_neurodivergent=MEDIUM\nevidence: SubscribeModal wrappers are plain `<div className=\"modal-backdrop\"/\"modal-container\">` (form view line 59, success view line 39); no role/aria-modal; trigger sets aria-haspopup=\"dialog\" (line 141)\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 activate \"Subscribe Now\" with a screen reader; no dialog role/name is announced and the virtual cursor reads background content\nexpected_behavior: SR announces \"Subscribe to Updates, dialog\"; background removed from the accessibility tree\nactual_behavior: overlay announced as inline content; background remains in reading order\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: modal-focus-not-moved-in-on-open\nfingerprint: a11y5f1a7c22de10\nsource: perspective-audit Keyboard & Motor Access checklist (item 4)\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 2.4.3 Focus Order / WAI-ARIA APG Dialog pattern (initial focus)\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 incorporates WCAG 2.0 A/AA; 2.4.3 is in scope\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: keyboard_motor=HIGH\nevidence: no useEffect/ref moves focus into the dialog on mount (lines 23-25); modal rendered after background nav (line 153)\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 open modal, press Tab; focus advances through background nav before reaching the dialog\nexpected_behavior: focus lands inside the dialog on open\nactual_behavior: focus remains on the trigger; next Tab enters background content\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: modal-focus-not-restored-on-close\nfingerprint: a11y5f2b9e41ab73\nsource: perspective-audit Keyboard & Motor Access checklist (item 4)\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 2.4.3 Focus Order / WAI-ARIA APG Dialog pattern (return focus)\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 incorporates WCAG 2.0 A/AA; 2.4.3 is in scope\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: keyboard_motor=HIGH\nevidence: handleClose (lines 127-130) never calls triggerRef.current.focus(); triggerRef attached at line 138 but unused\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 open then close the modal; focus drops to document body\nexpected_behavior: focus returns to the \"Subscribe Now\" trigger\nactual_behavior: focus lost to <body>; keyboard user loses place\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: modal-no-focus-containment-background-focusable\nfingerprint: a11y5f3c1d88f4a6\nsource: perspective-audit Keyboard & Motor Access checklist (item 4)\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 2.4.3 Focus Order / WAI-ARIA APG Dialog pattern (focus containment)\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 incorporates WCAG 2.0 A/AA; 2.4.3 is in scope\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: keyboard_motor=HIGH\nevidence: comment \"No focus trap logic \u2014 Tab exits into background page freely\" (line 25); background nav (lines 147-151) has no inert/aria-hidden\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 Tab repeatedly while modal open; focus enters background links beneath the dimmed backdrop\nexpected_behavior: Tab cycles only among the dialog's focusable elements\nactual_behavior: focus escapes to background content that is visually obscured by the backdrop\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: modal-dialog-missing-accessible-name\nfingerprint: a11y6f2d3a90c157\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic Structure checklist (item 11)\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 incorporates WCAG 2.0 A/AA; 4.1.2 is in scope\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=HIGH\nevidence: `<h2 id=\"modal-title\">` (line 64) is never referenced; no aria-labelledby/aria-label on the container (comment line 63)\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 once a dialog role is present, SR announces \"dialog\" with no title\nexpected_behavior: dialog announces its name \"Subscribe to Updates\"\nactual_behavior: dialog has no accessible name\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: modal-close-button-no-accessible-name\nfingerprint: a11y6f3e8b12d4c9\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic Structure checklist (item 11)\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 4.1.2 Name, Role, Value\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 incorporates WCAG 2.0 A/AA; 4.1.2 is in scope\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=HIGH, keyboard_motor=HIGH\nevidence: `<button className=\"modal-close\">\u00d7</button>` \u2014 form view lines 69-74, success view line 46; no aria-label\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 SR focuses close control; announces \"times\"/\"multiplication sign\"/\"button\", not \"Close\"\nexpected_behavior: control announces \"Close\" (or \"Close dialog\")\nactual_behavior: no meaningful accessible name; in the success view this is the only control\ntrend: new\n\n### A11y Evidence Finding\nfinding_id: modal-success-not-announced-no-live-region\nfingerprint: a11y6f4a5c73e820\nsource: perspective-audit Screen Reader & Semantic Structure checklist (item 12)\nwcag_or_apg: WCAG 2.2 SC 4.1.3 Status Messages\nsection_508_fpc_context: Revised Section 508 incorporates WCAG 2.0 A/AA; 4.1.3 is a WCAG 2.1 addition \u2014 verify against the applicable 508 baseline\nseverity: MAJOR\nperspective_alarms: screen_reader_semantic=HIGH\nevidence: success text `<p className=\"modal-success\">` (line 41) has no role=\"status\"/aria-live; submitted branch lines 32-49\nreproduction_steps: source review only \u2014 submit the form with a screen reader; the confirmation is not announced\nexpected_behavior: \"Thanks, \u2026 You're subscribed\" announced politely and/or focus moved to it\nactual_behavior: DOM swaps silently; no confirmation reaches the SR user\ntrend: new\n\n---\n\n## Perspective Audit Summary\n\n**Component/artifact reviewed:** SubscribeModal / SubscribePage (modal dialog with missing focus management and dialog semantics)\n**Perspectives escalated for deep review:** Keyboard & Motor Access (HIGH), Screen Reader & Semantic Structure (HIGH), Cognitive & Neurodivergent (MEDIUM)\n**Perspectives at LOW (not reviewed):** Magnification & Reflow, Environmental Contrast, Vestibular & Motion, Auditory Access\n\n### Findings by Severity\n\n| Severity | Count |\n|---|---|\n| CRITICAL | 1 |\n| MAJOR | 6 |\n| MINOR | 3 |\n| ENHANCEMENT | 0 |\n\n### Perspectives That Passed\n\nNone of the three escalated perspectives passed clean. Alarm calibration was confirmed accurate:\n- **Keyboard & Motor (HIGH):** confirmed \u2014 3 MAJOR + 1 MINOR, but no CRITICAL (fully operable, no keyboard trap). HIGH, not CRITICAL-saturated, was the right level.\n- **Screen Reader & Semantic (HIGH):** confirmed \u2014 1 CRITICAL + 3 MAJOR.\n- **Cognitive & Neurodivergent (MEDIUM):** confirmed \u2014 2 MINOR only, no red flags fired. MEDIUM was correctly calibrated.\n\n**Genuine strengths credited (not dead \"flag-everything\" output):** real semantic `<button>`/`<input>` elements throughout; form labels correctly associated via `htmlFor`/`id` (3.3.2 exemplary); logical heading hierarchy h1\u2192h2 (2.4.6); sufficient, consistent focus indicators on every control (2.4.7); `main`/`nav` landmarks present; plain-language content; user-triggered (not unprompted) modal; activation on up-event. The defects are concentrated in dialog semantics and focus lifecycle \u2014 not in the fundamentals.\n\n### Perspectives With Findings \u2014 Grouped by ARRM Role\n\n**Front-End Dev** *(primary owner of every finding \u2014 this is an implementation-defect fixture)*\n- No `role=\"dialog\"`/`aria-modal` \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 CRITICAL \u2014 4.1.2\n- Focus not moved into dialog on open \u2014 Keyboard & Motor \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 2.4.3\n- Focus not restored to trigger on close \u2014 Keyboard & Motor \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 2.4.3\n- No focus containment (background focusable behind modal) \u2014 Keyboard & Motor \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 2.4.3\n- Dialog has no accessible name (`aria-labelledby` unused) \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 4.1.2\n- Close \"\u00d7\" has no accessible name \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 4.1.2\n- Success confirmation not announced (no `aria-live`/`role=\"status\"`) \u2014 Screen Reader & Semantic \u2014 MAJOR \u2014 4.1.3\n- No Escape-key dismissal \u2014 Keyboard & Motor \u2014 MINOR \u2014 4.1.2 (APG convention)\n- Name/email inputs lack `autocomplete` \u2014 Cognitive & Neurodivergent \u2014 MINOR \u2014 1.3.5\n- No validation / error suggestion despite `required`+`noValidate` \u2014 Cognitive & Neurodivergent \u2014 MINOR \u2014 3.3.3 (+3.3.1)\n\n**Visual Design**\n- No primary-owned findings. (Contrast, reflow, focus-indicator visibility all pass or belong to LOW perspectives not in scope.)\n\n**UX Design**\n- No primary-owned findings, but named as **secondary** on the focus-lifecycle and dialog-interaction findings (5.1, 5.2, 5.3, 5.4, 6.1, 6.4, 7.2): UX must define the intended dialog open/close/focus-return pattern the developer implements.\n\n**Content Author**\n- No primary-owned findings, but named as **secondary** on the accessible-name findings (6.2, 6.3): supply the dialog title relationship intent and the close-button label wording.\n\n### Open Questions Requiring Human Verification\n\n- **Close-button label wording** \u2014 \"Close\" vs \"Close dialog\" vs \"Dismiss\" is a Content Author decision; the *absence* of a name is proven from source, but the chosen string is not. [Human verification required \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source]\n- **Validation intent** \u2014 whether the `required` + `noValidate` + no-op submit is a deliberate fixture simplification or a genuine product gap needs UX/product confirmation before deciding how far the error-handling fix goes. [Human verification required \u2014 cannot be confirmed from source]\n- No media or informative images are present, so no caption/transcript/audio-description/alt-text verification items apply.\n\nAll other findings are **code-level** and enforceable directly from source (file:line evidence supplied).\n\n### Recommended Next Step\n\n**BLOCK.** One CRITICAL finding is present \u2014 the overlay has no dialog role or `aria-modal`, which (with the trigger's `aria-haspopup=\"dialog\"` promise) leaves screen-reader users unable to perceive that a dialog exists or where it begins and ends. Six MAJOR findings compound this across the focus lifecycle and status announcement. Do not ship until at least the CRITICAL and the six MAJOR findings are resolved, then re-test with `a11y-test` (keyboard walkthrough for focus move-in / containment / restoration, and a screen-reader pass verifying dialog role, name, and the success live-region announcement).\n",
